00036 template <typename A, typename BI>
00037 BI destroy (A& a, BI b, BI e) {
00038     while (b != e) {
00039         --e;
00040         a.destroy(&*e);}
00041     return b;}

00043 // ------------------
00044 // uninitialized_copy
00045 // ------------------
00046 
00047 template <typename A, typename II, typename BI>
00048 BI uninitialized_copy (A& a, II b, II e, BI x) {
00049     BI p = x;
00050     try {
00051         while (b != e) {
00052             a.construct(&*x, *b);
00053             ++b;
00054             ++x;}}
00055     catch (...) {
00056         destroy(a, p, x);
00057         throw;}
00058     return x;}
00059 
00060 // ------------------
00061 // uninitialized_fill
00062 // ------------------
00063 
00064 template <typename A, typename BI, typename U>
00065 BI uninitialized_fill (A& a, BI b, BI e, const U& v) {
00066     BI p = b;
00067     try {
00068         while (b != e) {
00069             a.construct(&*b, v);
00070             ++b;}}
00071     catch (...) {
00072         destroy(a, p, b);
00073         throw;}
00074     return e;}

00516         explicit Deque (size_type s, const_reference v = value_type(), const allocator_type& a = allocator_type()) : _inner_alloc(a), INNER_SIZE(10) {
00517                 // Keeps track in the even that we have a non divisible size by 10 to add an extra spot in the physical array
00518                 size_type numInArray = s/INNER_SIZE+(s%INNER_SIZE ==0 ? 0:1);
00519                 pointer_pointer start = _outer_pfront = _outer_lfront = _outer_alloc.allocate(numInArray);
00520                 size_type allocated = 0,skip;
00521                 _outer_pback = _outer_lback = _outer_pfront + numInArray;
00522 
00523                 //Creating Inner Arrays
00524                 while(start < _outer_pback) {
00525                         *start = _inner_alloc.allocate(INNER_SIZE);
00526                         allocated += INNER_SIZE;
00527                 ++start;
00528                 }
00529 
00530                 //Total number of spaces allocated minus the number of the size requested divided by 2 to help make it center loaded. 
00531                 skip = (allocated - s)/2;
00532 
00533                 //Set the logical array pointers
00534                 _front = (*_outer_lfront)+skip;
00535                 _back = *(_outer_lback-1)+(INNER_SIZE-((allocated-s)-skip));
00536

00538                 uninitialized_fill(_inner_alloc,begin(),end(),v);
00539             assert(valid());}

00828         void push_back (const_reference e) {
00829 
00830         //If our pointers are null, make a deque
00831            if(_outer_pfront == 0){
00832                 _outer_pfront = _outer_lfront = _outer_alloc.allocate(1);
00833                 _outer_pback = _outer_lback = _outer_pfront+1;
00834                 
00835                 *_outer_lfront = _inner_alloc.allocate(INNER_SIZE);
00836         
00837                 //Make it center loaded
00838                 _front = *_outer_lfront +(INNER_SIZE/2);
00839 
00840                 _back  = _front +1;     
00841                 
00842                 *_front = e;
00843                 }
00844 
00845         //If you already have some space in the back of the array
00846         else if(_back != *(_outer_lback -1) + INNER_SIZE){
00847         
00848                 *_back = e;
00849 
00850                 ++_back;}
00851 
00852         //Else you are at your last element of the last inner array. Time to resize.
00853         else{
00854                 
00855         //Check to see if you have space in the physical array
00856         if(_outer_lback == _outer_pback){
00857         difference_type newsize = 2*(_outer_pback - _outer_pfront);
00858         pointer_pointer tempfront =  _outer_alloc.allocate(newsize);
00859         pointer_pointer temp = tempfront;
00860         pointer_pointer tempiterator = _outer_pfront;
00861         
00862         //Copy current elements
00863         while(tempiterator != _outer_pback){
00864                 _outer_alloc.construct(temp, *tempiterator);
00865                 _outer_alloc.destroy(tempiterator);
00866                 ++temp;
00867                 ++tempiterator;}
00868         _outer_alloc.deallocate(_outer_pfront,(_outer_pback-_outer_pfront));
00869 
00870         _outer_pfront = _outer_lfront = tempfront;
00871         _outer_lback = temp;
00872         _outer_pback = tempfront + newsize;}
00873 
00874         //add the e
00875         ++_outer_lback;
00876         _back = *(_outer_lback -1);
00877         *_back = e;
00878         ++_back;
00879         }
00880                 
00881             assert(valid());}

00959                 pop_back();
00960                 --my_size;
00961             }
00962             while(s > my_size) {
00963                 push_back(v);
00964                 ++my_size;
00965             }
00966             assert(valid());}

00970         // ----

00975         size_type size () const {
00976             if(_outer_pfront==0) return 0;
00977             return ((_outer_lback - _outer_lfront)*INNER_SIZE) - (_front - *_outer_lfront) - ((*(_outer_lback-1)+INNER_SIZE) - _back);}

00987         void swap (Deque& that) {
00988             if(_inner_alloc == that._inner_alloc && _outer_alloc == that._outer_alloc) {
00989                     std::swap(_outer_pfront,that._outer_pfront);
00990                     std::swap(_outer_lfront,that._outer_lfront);
00991                     std::swap(_outer_pback, that._outer_pback);
00992                     std::swap(_outer_lback, that._outer_lback);
00993                     std::swap(_front,       that._front);
00994                     std::swap(_back,        that._back);
00995             }
00996             else {
00997                     Deque temp(*this);
00998                     *this = that;
00999                     that = temp;
01000             }
01001             assert(valid());}};
